  "texts": [
    "The left hand side says that y ⊑ max{z ∈ S ′ | R ′ i (z) ⊆ ↓x}.",
    "If f ′ i (y) ⊑ x, then since f ′ i (y) = max(R ′ i (y)), R ′ i (y) ⊆ ↓x, so y ⊑ max{z ∈ S ′ | R ′ i (z) ⊆ ↓x}.",
    "In the other direction, if y ⊑ max{z ∈ S ′ | R ′ i (z) ⊆ ↓x}, then by Fact 4.43, we have f ′ i (y) ⊑ f ′ i (max{z ∈ S ′ | R ′ i (z) ⊆ ↓x}), and given f ′ i (z) = max(R ′ i (z)), we have f ′ i (max{z ∈ S ′ | R ′ i (z) ⊆ ↓x}) ⊑ x, so f ′ i (y) ⊑ x.Part 5 is by an easy induction on φ using Fact 2.5.1, left to the reader.",
    "For part 6, we already have from part 5 that if φ is satisfiable over F, then φ is satisfiable over F b.",
    "For the other direction, suppose φ is satisfied in some algebraic model ⟨F b, θ⟩."
